---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="SMC SuperFIB" description="Distributed‑systems solution for trading signals.">
  <div class="hand-drawn-frame p-8 space-y-8">
    <h1 class="hand-drawn-heading text-3xl">SMC SuperFIB</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-mid">A distributed‑systems solution that synchronises a Pine Script indicator, a PHP/WordPress REST API (source of truth), MT5 Expert Advisors, and a React dashboard.</p>

    <figure class="hand-drawn-figure max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <img src="/images/diagram-system/superfib.svg"
           alt="Hub‑and‑spoke flow: Pine Script Indicator → PHP/WordPress REST API (source of truth) ← MT5 Expert Advisors → React Dashboard."
           class="w-full rounded-lg" />
      <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-mid mt-3">
        Hub‑and‑spoke data flow – PHP/WordPress API is the central source of truth.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div>
      <h2 class="hand-drawn-heading text-2xl mb-4">Engineering Challenges Solved</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-mid">
        <li>Backend‑as‑source‑of‑truth across 3+ runtimes</li>
        <li>Broker time normalisation (UTC+2 offset handling)</li>
        <li>Staleness gates &amp; <code>STALE_HELD</code> blocker logic</li>
        <li>Cross‑platform parity audits (chop‑threshold drift, HTF bias fixes)</li>
        <li>Nearest‑minute rounding &amp; cached broker offsets to eliminate jitter</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>